funny coming from a guy

250
00:11:29,750 --> 00:11:31,041
whose whole body is shaking.

251
00:11:31,125 --> 00:11:32,458
[USAMARU]
What?!

252
00:11:32,541 --> 00:11:33,875
No, I'm not shaking with fear;
I'm shaking with rage!

253
00:11:33,958 --> 00:11:35,750
I'm about to kill
this ghost, man!

254
00:11:35,833 --> 00:11:37,083
[YUTO]
All right!

255
00:11:37,166 --> 00:11:38,791
You guys ready to get this
freak show on the road?

256
00:11:38,875 --> 00:11:39,875
[GROUP]
Yeah!

257
00:11:39,958 --> 00:11:41,791
[USAMARU]
Uh... Y-Yeah, let's do it.

258
00:11:48,875 --> 00:11:51,125
[doorbell rings]

259
00:11:51,208 --> 00:11:52,166
[KURUMI gasps]

260
00:11:52,250 --> 00:11:54,333
You're the rookie battle winner.

261
00:11:54,416 --> 00:11:56,083
I'm Otone Fujishiro.

262
00:11:56,166 --> 00:11:58,250
I apologize for
calling so late, ma'am.

263
00:11:58,333 --> 00:12:01,041
I was hoping to speak with
Seisa Mikagura if possible.

264
00:12:01,125 --> 00:12:05,166
Unfortunately, my lady has gone
to bed and is not available.

265
00:12:05,250 --> 00:12:06,041
[SEISA]
It's okay.

266
00:12:06,125 --> 00:12:07,125
[KURUMI gasps]

267
00:12:25,375 --> 00:12:27,041
[ERUNA]
Come out, little ghostie.

268
00:12:27,125 --> 00:12:29,583
You can trust us.
We're not gonna hurt you!

269
00:12:29,666 --> 00:12:32,250
Little ghostie,
are you even real?

270
00:12:32,333 --> 00:12:33,500
[USAMARU groans]

271
00:12:41,125 --> 00:12:42,500
[USAMARU gasps]

272
00:12:42,583 --> 00:12:44,958
[screams]

273
00:12:45,041 --> 00:12:47,125
Over there!

274
00:12:47,208 --> 00:12:48,833
--[USUMARU cries]
--Will you keep it down?!

275
00:12:48,916 --> 00:12:49,916
[NYAMIRIN]
Yes, hush it.

276
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:51,583
You're going to scare
the ghost away!

277
00:12:51,666 --> 00:12:54,500
But I saw things!
Horrible things!

278
00:12:55,583 --> 00:12:57,333
[USAMARU]
Where'd it go?

279
00:12:57,416 --> 00:12:58,416
[TONKYUN]
What are we looking at?

280
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:00,333
No way! Did you find the ghost?

281
00:13:02,791 --> 00:13:05,125
[ERUNA]
Usamaru! There's nothing there! 

282
00:13:05,208 --> 00:13:07,500
No... It's not a ghost.

283
00:13:07,583 --> 00:13:09,125
What I saw looked like
part of the school

284
00:13:09,208 --> 00:13:10,875
was collapsing in on itself.

285
00:13:10,958 --> 00:13:13,000
[TONKYUN] Nothing appears
to be collapsing to me.

286
00:13:13,083 --> 00:13:14,083
Nope, me either.

287
00:13:14,166 --> 00:13:15,166
Oh...

288
00:13:15,250 --> 00:13:17,416
Maybe I just... imagined it.

289
00:13:21,541 --> 00:13:22,583
[TONKYUN]
According to the data

290
00:13:22,666 --> 00:13:24,791
given to us by the
newspaper club,

291
00:13:24,875 --> 00:13:27,291
the majority of eyewitness
reports about the ghost

292
00:13:27,375 --> 00:13:29,250
are right around this corner.

293
00:13:29,333 --> 00:13:30,166
[ERUNA gasps]

294
00:13:30,250 --> 00:13:32,250
Hey! My old home!

295
00:13:32,333 --> 00:13:34,666
I slept right here.
Oh, nostalgia.

296
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:36,333
Thanks to not being
a member of a club,

297
00:13:36,416 --> 00:13:37,916
Eruna was forced to
live in this hallway

298
00:13:38,000 --> 00:13:40,166
before she moved into
Seisa's mansion, ryui.

299
00:13:40,250 --> 00:13:41,791
Moments like these
make you think about

300
00:13:41,875 --> 00:13:43,500
what life was like
on the other side.

301
00:13:43,583 --> 00:13:45,750
Not to mention how far
I've come since then!

302
00:13:45,833 --> 00:13:46,708
[KATAI giggles]

303
00:13:46,791 --> 00:13:48,291
It's funny now,

304
00:13:48,375 --> 00:13:50,375
but I remember when Eruna would
hop around in her sleeping bag,

305
00:13:50,458 --> 00:13:52,166
and it would
completely terrify me

306
00:13:52,250 --> 00:13:55,041
until I'd finally
realize it was her.

307
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:56,583
Oh yeah. I always thought it was

308
00:13:56,666 --> 00:13:58,625
way too much trouble to get out
of the bag, so I'd just jump

309
00:13:58,708 --> 00:14:00,666
to wherever I wanted to
go while I was still inside it!

310
00:14:00,750 --> 00:14:02,000
Every time I saw you,

311
00:14:02,083 --> 00:14:03,791
I thought for a sec you
were a ghost haunting me.

312
00:14:03,875 --> 00:14:04,750
[YUTO]
Hm.

313
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:06,166
Hold on, you guys.

314
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:07,791
Hey, you know all those
eyewitness accounts

315
00:14:07,875 --> 00:14:09,583
reporting the ghost to
be right around here?

316
00:14:09,666 --> 00:14:11,208
What did they say exactly?

317
00:14:11,291 --> 00:14:13,708
[TONKYUN]
According to the data we've got:

318
00:14:13,791 --> 00:14:15,166
The ghost was an eerie face

319
00:14:15,250 --> 00:14:17,750
that would appear out of
nowhere in the darkness.

320
00:14:17,833 --> 00:14:19,500
That's what they said.

321
00:14:19,583 --> 00:14:21,166
So you guys are
probably thinking

322
00:14:21,250 --> 00:14:22,625
what I'm thinking, right?

323
00:14:22,708 --> 00:14:24,250
[TONKYUN] You mean that the
ghost must have been Eruna

324
00:14:24,333 --> 00:14:26,666
wandering around
in her sleeping bag?

325
00:14:26,750 --> 00:14:27,708
Eh?

326
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:31,333
What? Really?

327
00:14:31,416 --> 00:14:33,250
[laughs] No, that's hilarious!

328
00:14:33,333 --> 00:14:34,375
You're so stupid.

329
00:14:34,458 --> 00:14:35,458
Seriously?!

330
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:37,041
That's kind of a letdown

331
00:14:37,125 --> 00:14:38,875
after we were thinking we were
gonna find a real life ghost!

332
00:14:38,958 --> 00:14:40,166
[TONKYUN]
This is a problem.

333
00:14:40,250 --> 00:14:41,416
You know that, right?

334
00:14:41,500 --> 00:14:42,791
No?

335
00:14:42,875 --> 00:14:44,416
[TONKYUN] When Rumina
asked if you were the ghost,

336
00:14:44,500 --> 00:14:45,291
you denied it.

337
00:14:45,375 --> 00:14:46,750
It'll look like you lied to her.

338
00:14:46,833 --> 00:14:47,958
[ERUNA gasps]

339
00:14:48,041 --> 00:14:49,125
[RUMINA] You knew at
the time you were making

340
00:14:49,208 --> 00:14:50,458
a fool out of the
newspaper club.

341
00:14:50,541 --> 00:14:52,333
Now, we have to fight to
get our good name back,

342
00:14:52,416 --> 00:14:55,708
and it's completely your fault.

343
00:14:55,791 --> 00:14:56,708
--[ERUNA whimpers]
--For real,

344
00:14:56,791 --> 00:14:58,208
she is gonna be
so pissed at you.

345
00:14:58,291 --> 00:14:59,708
[NYAMIRIN]
Unbelievably pissed.

346
00:14:59,791 --> 00:15:01,208
[ERUNA]
Ugh...

347
00:15:01,291 --> 00:15:02,125
[gasps]

348
00:15:02,208 --> 00:15:03,875
Oh, right! Bimii!

349
00:15:03,958 --> 00:15:05,791
Would you do me a favor?

350
00:15:05,875 --> 00:15:06,958
[BIMII]
Eh...

351
00:15:07,041 --> 00:15:09,250
[owl hooting]

352
00:15:14,583 --> 00:15:16,083
[RUMINA gasps, grunts]

353
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:19,125
Hey! Who are you, and
are you the perpetrator

354
00:15:19,208 --> 00:15:21,458
purportedly pretending
to be a poltergeist?

355
00:15:22,083 --> 00:15:23,500
[RUMINA]
Come back!

356
00:15:23,583 --> 00:15:24,625
[GHOST moans]

357
00:15:29,375 --> 00:15:30,916
Huh-uh.

358
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,541
I didn't just see a
genuine ghost, did I?

359
00:15:33,625 --> 00:15:36,583
[screams]

360
00:15:38,791 --> 00:15:42,083
I have no idea how that
could've fooled anyone, ryui.

361
00:15:42,166 --> 00:15:43,125
[gasps]

362
00:15:45,333 --> 00:15:47,625
[BIMII gasps]

363
00:15:57,916 --> 00:15:58,875
[KUZURYU]
Huh?

364
00:16:01,708 --> 00:16:03,083
[OTONE]
Answer the question, Seisa.

365
00:16:03,166 --> 00:16:04,750
It's not that hard.

366
00:16:04,833 --> 00:16:06,250
Fujishiro wants
to know the truth.

367
00:16:06,333 --> 00:16:09,041
She wants to know why you
refuse to go see Eruna.

368
00:16:09,125 --> 00:16:10,458
[SEISA sighs]

369
00:16:10,541 --> 00:16:12,458
And here I thought your
presence would be interesting.

370
00:16:12,541 --> 00:16:14,833
Eruna formed a new
club for you, Seisa.

371
00:16:14,916 --> 00:16:17,000
You know she did,
so don't deny it.

372
00:16:17,083 --> 00:16:18,666
Are you just égoïste?

373
00:16:21,166 --> 00:16:22,791
[OTONE] Seems you're
selfish because even though

374
00:16:22,875 --> 00:16:25,791
Eruna worked hard to form a club
specifically to make you happy,

375
00:16:25,875 --> 00:16:27,791
doesn't look like you're
too happy for her.

376
00:16:27,875 --> 00:16:29,458
And even though Eruna
has been waiting for you

377
00:16:29,541 --> 00:16:30,833
to show up in support of her,

378
00:16:30,916 --> 00:16:33,000
you don't seem to want
to do that, either.

379
00:16:33,083 --> 00:16:34,166
Is it pride?

380
00:16:34,250 --> 00:16:35,625
Will your precious
pride not allow you to

381
00:16:35,708 --> 00:16:37,541
walk over there
and be kind to her?

382
00:16:38,625 --> 00:16:40,250
Why? Because if Eruna
wants to see you,

383
00:16:40,333 --> 00:16:42,125
she should be the one
making the effort?

384
00:16:42,208 --> 00:16:43,875
Are you so special that
you can't be bothered

385
00:16:43,958 --> 00:16:46,000
to make an effort for
anyone other than yourself?

386
00:16:46,083 --> 00:16:47,041
Who are you?!

387
00:16:47,125 --> 00:16:48,833
Rather, who do
you think you are?

388
00:16:48,916 --> 00:16:49,875
A celebrity?

389
00:16:49,958 --> 00:16:51,458
The Queen of Sheba?

390
00:16:51,541 --> 00:16:54,125
Are you teasing her on purpose
to feel better about yourself?

391
00:16:54,208 --> 00:16:56,333
Having fun leaving her
hanging like this?

392
00:16:56,416 --> 00:16:57,625
You'd think you were
some child star

393
00:16:57,708 --> 00:16:58,791
trying to make a comeback

394
00:16:58,875 --> 00:17:00,208
but afraid everyone
will think you suck,

395
00:17:00,291 --> 00:17:01,958
so you say you've been
spending time in the "theatre"

396
00:17:02,041 --> 00:17:03,291
because you're a "real artist"

397
00:17:03,375 --> 00:17:04,625
when really, you're just
an attention-seeking jerk

398
00:17:04,708 --> 00:17:05,833
who wants to be worshipped!

399
00:17:05,916 --> 00:17:07,375
Well, guess what.
It's not very nice,

400
00:17:07,458 --> 00:17:09,875
and it's an unbelievably
cruel way to treat Eruna.

401
00:17:09,958 --> 00:17:10,708
[SEISA chuckles]

402
00:17:10,791 --> 00:17:12,041
Not that it matters to me,

403
00:17:12,125 --> 00:17:14,291
but you never actually
lived abroad, did you?

404
00:17:14,375 --> 00:17:15,291
[OTONE gasps]

405
00:17:15,375 --> 00:17:16,666
Did you not notice?

406
00:17:16,750 --> 00:17:18,375
You stopped trying to
Frenchify your words

407
00:17:18,458 --> 00:17:20,250
somewhere in the middle of
that darling little speech.

408
00:17:20,333 --> 00:17:22,791
So what?! That has nothing
to do with anything right now!

409
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:24,375
Let me ask you.

410
00:17:24,458 --> 00:17:27,000
So what if I am all those
things you just called me?

411
00:17:27,083 --> 00:17:30,208
How is my life any
of your business?

412
00:17:30,291 --> 00:17:31,458
Why bother getting angry

413
00:17:31,541 --> 00:17:34,125
about a situation that
in no way involves you?

414
00:17:36,916 --> 00:17:38,583
[OTONE]
Because...

415
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:43,500
[ERUNA laughs]

416
00:17:43,583 --> 00:17:46,083
Hey, at least we can officially
close that case, amiright?

417
00:17:46,166 --> 00:17:47,708
[USAMARU]
Not so fast!

418
00:17:47,791 --> 00:17:49,250
'Kay.

419
00:17:49,333 --> 00:17:51,625
Eruna, I get that you were the
ghost everyone else saw, but

420
00:17:51,708 --> 00:17:54,000
what the hell was
behind what I saw?

421
00:17:54,083 --> 00:17:55,208
[YUTO]
Are you talking about

422
00:17:55,291 --> 00:17:56,208
when your imagination
got the best of you?

423
00:17:56,291 --> 00:17:57,625
Shut up!

424
00:17:57,708 --> 00:17:58,791
That's not what happened.
The school was collapsing!

425
00:17:58,875 --> 00:17:59,666
It's cool.

426
00:17:59,750 --> 00:18:01,000
Calm down. We get it.

427
00:18:01,083 --> 00:18:02,125
I don't know about you guys,

428
00:18:02,208 --> 00:18:03,500
but I'm still kinda freaked out

429
00:18:03,583 --> 00:18:06,083
that Mr. Bimii was even
able to turn into a human.

430
00:18:06,166 --> 00:18:07,416
[TONKYUN]
His method of transformation

431
00:18:07,500 --> 00:18:08,583
didn't help, either.

432
00:18:08,666 --> 00:18:10,625
Oh yeah, that threw
me for a loop, too.

433
00:18:10,708 --> 00:18:13,833
What was that factory looking
place supposed to be anyway?

434
00:18:13,916 --> 00:18:15,458
[TONKYUN]
Probably smart if we just forget

435
00:18:15,541 --> 00:18:17,125
that whole thing ever happened.

436
00:18:17,208 --> 00:18:19,708
[KATAI] Mr. Bimii sure is
taking a long time catching up.

437
00:18:19,791 --> 00:18:22,375
I bet he's just floating
around being lazy.

438
00:18:22,458 --> 00:18:24,500
Hey! What's up, Enoyan?

439
00:18:24,583 --> 00:18:26,000
Is everything okay?

440
00:18:26,083 --> 00:18:26,791
Oh!

441
00:18:26,875 --> 00:18:28,125
I bet after drinking milk

442
00:18:28,208 --> 00:18:29,500
all by your lonesome self
in the dark of night,

443
00:18:29,583 --> 00:18:31,583
you started to long for
company and came to see me.

444
00:18:31,666 --> 00:18:32,791
Such a sweet heart!

445
00:18:32,875 --> 00:18:34,583
And of course, you can
hang out with us!

446
00:18:34,666 --> 00:18:36,583
That's not it, stupid.

447
00:18:36,666 --> 00:18:39,208
But now that I think about
it, maybe I'm the stupid one

448
00:18:39,291 --> 00:18:41,541
for thinking I needed to
tell you what I just saw.

449
00:18:41,625 --> 00:18:42,791
[ERUNA]
Huh?

450
00:18:42,875 --> 00:18:44,375
[KUZURYU] Has to do with
that girl from your club

451
00:18:44,458 --> 00:18:46,666
with the purple
hair and Seisa.

452
00:18:46,750 --> 00:18:49,250
Best-case scenario:
they're about to fight.

453
00:18:49,333 --> 00:18:50,458
[ERUNA]
Huh?

454
00:18:51,625 --> 00:18:53,750
[ERUNA] Otone and
Seisa are gonna fight?

455
00:18:53,833 --> 00:18:55,833
Your club doesn't have
anything to do with me,

456
00:18:55,916 --> 00:18:57,875
and I don't have
anything to do with it.

457
00:18:57,958 --> 00:18:59,916
Why waste your time
worrying about my actions

458
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:02,291
when you can do
whatever you want?

459
00:19:02,375 --> 00:19:05,791
[OTONE] Because inside
Eruna, you're always there.

460
00:19:05,875 --> 00:19:07,375
[SEISA gasps]

461
00:19:07,458 --> 00:19:10,750
[OTONE] Because no matter how
much fun we might have together,

462
00:19:10,833 --> 00:19:12,875
she'd have more fun if
you were there, too.

463
00:19:12,958 --> 00:19:15,666
You have to know she's
always thinking about you.

464
00:19:17,166 --> 00:19:19,833
[OTONE] Fuji worries because
no matter how hard she tries,

465
00:19:19,916 --> 00:19:21,583
Eruna keeps you in
a forbidden place

466
00:19:21,666 --> 00:19:23,625
that Fujishiro cannot enter.

467
00:19:25,166 --> 00:19:26,125
Wow.

468
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:28,000
It's really not
that big of a deal.

469
00:19:28,083 --> 00:19:29,666
I just don't get you.

470
00:19:29,750 --> 00:19:31,250
If I were in your shoes, I--

471
00:19:31,333 --> 00:19:34,250
I would naturally want to stay
as far away from you as I could.

472
00:19:34,333 --> 00:19:35,625
[OTONE] That might
be the smartest move,

473
00:19:35,708 --> 00:19:37,250
but it would be selfish.

474
00:19:37,333 --> 00:19:40,291
Besides Fujishiro isn't
worried about herself.

475
00:19:40,375 --> 00:19:42,875
All I want is for
Eruna to be happy!

476
00:19:44,541 --> 00:19:46,041
She understands me.

477
00:19:46,125 --> 00:19:49,291
She was the first person to give
me a chance and be my friend.

478
00:19:49,375 --> 00:19:51,541
To me, that girl is more
precious and cherished

479
00:19:51,625 --> 00:19:53,250
than you will ever know.

480
00:19:53,333 --> 00:19:54,958
[And what I feel for
her is stronger than

481
00:19:55,041 --> 00:19:57,083
what anyone else might claim.

482
00:19:57,166 --> 00:19:59,291
That includes you, too, Seisa.

483
00:19:59,375 --> 00:20:00,500
Believe it.

484
00:20:02,583 --> 00:20:03,833
[OTONE]
Now you understand why

485
00:20:03,916 --> 00:20:06,875
I will do whatever it
takes to make you listen.

486
00:20:06,958 --> 00:20:08,333
[SEISA]
Hm.

487
00:20:08,416 --> 00:20:10,583
Whatever it takes, my goodness.

488
00:20:10,666 --> 00:20:11,791
What could you do?

489
00:20:11,875 --> 00:20:12,875
Anything?

490
00:20:12,958 --> 00:20:14,791
[OTONE]
Won't know unless I try, will I?

491
00:20:14,875 --> 00:20:16,375
I do hope winning
the rookie battle

492
00:20:16,458 --> 00:20:19,958
didn't make you too
confident, Otone, dear.

493
00:20:20,041 --> 00:20:21,458
You wouldn't want to get hurt.

494
00:20:27,500 --> 00:20:29,416
Anticomplex!

495
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,708
Snake!

496
00:20:35,750 --> 00:20:37,166
[OTONE grunts]

497
00:20:37,250 --> 00:20:39,333
Are you seriously planning
to fight me with pink ribbons?

498
00:20:39,416 --> 00:20:40,625
[OTONE grunts]

499
00:20:40,708 --> 00:20:41,791
Sword!

500
00:20:43,208 --> 00:20:44,166
[SEISA grunts]

501
00:20:47,041 --> 00:20:48,083
[SEISA gasps]

502
00:20:57,291 --> 00:20:57,750
[OTONE grunts]

503
00:20:57,833 --> 00:21:00,750
[ERUNA panting]

504
00:21:00,833 --> 00:21:02,208
I don't get any of this!

505
00:21:02,291 --> 00:21:04,208
Why would they even be together?

506
00:21:04,291 --> 00:21:05,250
[gasps]

507
00:21:09,875 --> 00:21:12,125
Oh no. I'm too late!

508
00:21:14,083 --> 00:21:15,666
[SEISA grunts]

509
00:21:15,750 --> 00:21:16,708
[gasps]

510
00:21:20,875 --> 00:21:21,708
Killing Art, go.

511
00:21:21,791 --> 00:21:22,916
[OTONE grunts]

512
00:21:33,041 --> 00:21:34,500
Rain down.

513
00:21:34,583 --> 00:21:36,208
[SEISA gasps]

514
00:21:36,291 --> 00:21:39,208
Fuji thought you were finally
going to use Killing Art.

515
00:21:39,291 --> 00:21:40,583
[SEISA gasps]

516
00:21:40,666 --> 00:21:42,083
Who's too confident, now?

517
00:21:42,166 --> 00:21:43,791
You shouldn't
underestimate Fuji.

518
00:21:43,875 --> 00:21:44,958
[SEISA grunts]

519
00:21:45,041 --> 00:21:46,958
So do you think you're
too good for this?

520
00:21:47,041 --> 00:21:48,708
Don't wanna waste your
treasured ability

521
00:21:48,791 --> 00:21:51,541
on such a pathetic loser?

522
00:21:51,625 --> 00:21:52,791
Is that how it is, Seisa?

523
00:21:52,875 --> 00:21:54,666
You can't be bothered
to take out the trash?

524
00:21:54,750 --> 00:21:56,500
Or is it so you have
an excuse to use

525
00:21:56,583 --> 00:21:59,083
when you get your ass
kicked by Fujishiro?

526
00:21:59,166 --> 00:22:00,500
You won't escape.

527
00:22:05,458 --> 00:22:06,583
[SEISA yelps]

528
00:22:06,666 --> 00:22:09,416
[grunts]

529
00:22:10,500 --> 00:22:12,375
[OTONE]
Sword.

530
00:22:20,375 --> 00:22:23,708
[OTONE] Even now, you refuse
use your ability on Fuji?

531
00:22:23,791 --> 00:22:27,541
If you'd rather me win than
use Killing Art, then so be it.

532
00:22:27,625 --> 00:22:30,583
When you lose,
remember, no excuses!

533
00:22:30,666 --> 00:22:31,958
[ERUNA]
Otone, don't!

534
00:22:32,041 --> 00:22:33,041
[OTONE gasps]

535
00:22:33,125 --> 00:22:35,500
[ERUNA panting]

536
00:22:38,416 --> 00:22:39,708
[OTONE growls]

537
00:22:41,291 --> 00:22:43,333
What's going on?

538
00:22:43,416 --> 00:22:45,083
One of you tell me!

539
00:24:18,208 --> 00:24:21,125
[HIMI] Hey, hold on! We aren't
far from the last episode,

540
00:24:21,208 --> 00:24:24,541
so why haven't I shown up yet
in a single preview?! How rude!

541
00:24:24,625 --> 00:24:25,541
[ERUNA]
Don't worry, Himi!

542
00:24:25,625 --> 00:24:26,958
I've been saving
this one for you!

543
00:24:27,041 --> 00:24:28,958
Go ahead and preview
to your heart's content!

544
00:24:29,041 --> 00:24:30,583
[HIMI]
Really? Here I go, then!

545
00:24:30,666 --> 00:24:32,208
[KURUMI]
Just a moment, please.

546
00:24:32,291 --> 00:24:35,041
I haven't been included in
a single preview, either.

547
00:24:35,125 --> 00:24:36,750
[ERUNA] Why did I not
think of putting Miss Kurumi

548
00:24:36,833 --> 00:24:38,166
and Himi together before?!

549
00:24:38,250 --> 00:24:40,166
Well, then, ladies, knock
us out with a new preview

550
00:24:40,250 --> 00:24:41,791
that no one has
ever, ever heard!

551
00:24:41,875 --> 00:24:43,333
[BIMII]
Hey, hold on a minute, ladies.

552
00:24:43,416 --> 00:24:45,250
Don't forget that I have
yet to do any previews

553
00:24:45,333 --> 00:24:46,333
in my human form.

554
00:24:46,416 --> 00:24:47,666
[ERUNA]
Bimii!

555
00:24:47,750 --> 00:24:49,500
[HIMI] Meh... Thanks,
but no thanks, Mr. Bimii.

556
00:24:49,583 --> 00:24:51,791
I think I can handle
this preview on my own.

557
00:24:51,875 --> 00:24:52,916
[BIMII]
Negative.

558
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:54,416
I've got two hundred
and eighty-seven,

559
00:24:54,500 --> 00:24:56,041
nine hundred and
twenty-eight thousand

560
00:24:56,125 --> 00:24:58,583
nationwide fans waiting
for this moment.

561
00:24:58,666 --> 00:25:01,041
I can't give that up, even
for you, darling Himi.

562
00:25:01,125 --> 00:25:02,541
[ERUNA] Then why don't
we do it all at once?

563
00:25:02,625 --> 00:25:04,958
[KURUMI] Because we hardly
need some lame preview

564
00:25:05,041 --> 00:25:07,500
that sounds like a bunch of
pathetic students holding hands,

565
00:25:07,583 --> 00:25:10,208
so they can all cross
the finish line at once.

566
00:25:10,291 --> 00:25:12,666
Everyone can't
always get a medal.

567
00:25:12,750 --> 00:25:15,166
Next time, "Nostalgic Triangle".

568
00:25:15,250 --> 00:25:18,375
[HIMI] Aw! You went and said it!
No fair, Miss Kurumi!

569
00:25:18,458 --> 00:25:20,375
[BIMII] They call that
stealing a march, mecha!

570
00:25:20,458 --> 00:25:22,166
You're a disgrace
as a teacher, mecha!

571
00:25:22,250 --> 00:25:23,500
[ERUNA]
Bimii, calm down!

572
00:25:23,583 --> 00:25:25,208
You're ending your sentences
with "mecha" again!

573
00:25:25,291 --> 00:25:28,791
[KURUMI] Next time, Lady Seisa's
past will finally be revealed.

574
00:25:28,875 --> 00:25:31,125
[ERUNA]
What? Seisa's past, what?!

575
00:25:31,208 --> 00:25:32,791
Now my heart's all a flutter!

